<subSubSection id="C34376A6FFDB4D130BF8FAE3FD4B15E6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BE6252DFFDB4D130BF8FAE3FD4B15E6" blockId="7.[151,1437,1357,1994]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130BF8FAE3FE2C152E" bold="true" box="[151,490,1357,1382]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Material examined. 51416#1</emphasis>
, one stem fragment c. 
<quantity id="4CA188C8FFDB4D130980FAE0FCF9152D" box="[751,831,1358,1382]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
long, no gonothecae; 
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130F55FAE3FB6F152E" bold="true" box="[1082,1193,1357,1382]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">52602#13</emphasis>
, four stem fragments up to 
<quantity id="4CA188C8FFDB4D130BB5FADCFEEC15C1" box="[218,298,1394,1418]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
long, with gonothecae; 
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130952FADFFD5915C2" bold="true" box="[573,671,1393,1418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">52701#6</emphasis>
, three stems up to 
<quantity id="4CA188C8FFDB4D130815FADCFC0C15C1" box="[890,970,1394,1418]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="70.0">70 mm</quantity>
high, with gonothecae; 
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130FB2FADFFA9215C2" bold="true" box="[1245,1364,1393,1418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">52701#48,</emphasis>
a few fragments up to 
<quantity id="4CA188C8FFDB4D130A22FA38FE5B15E5" box="[333,413,1430,1454]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="33.0">33 mm</quantity>
long, no gonothecae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34376A6FFDB4D130BA8FA17FC9916BA" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE6252DFFDB4D130BA8FA17FADD1676" blockId="7.[151,1437,1357,1994]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130BA8FA17FE9F159A" bold="true" box="[199,345,1465,1490]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description.</emphasis>
Polysiphonic stems, up to 
<quantity id="4CA188C8FFDB4D1309F7FA14FD2D1599" box="[664,747,1466,1490]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="70.0">70 mm</quantity>
high. Hydrorhiza rhizoidal, quite robust, formed by a few, basally polysiphonic stolons. Hydrothecae arising in an indefinite pattern. Hydrotheca (
<figureCitation id="136239A8FFDB4D130FDEFA73FAF715BE" box="[1201,1329,1501,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[266,1353,236,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[208,1380,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acryptolaria crassicaulis (Allman, 1888): A, hydrotheca; B, macrobasic mastigophore nematocyst (arrow). Cryptolarella abyssicola (Allman, 1888): C-D, hydrothecae; E, gonotheca. Lafoea dumosa (Fleming, 1820): F, hydrotheca; G, detail of basal part of hydrotheca; H, isorhiza nematocyst. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, C-F), 100 µm (G), 10 µm (B, H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1044778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3C–D</figureCitation>
) tubular, diameter roughly constant throughout its length. Hydrotheca bent outwards at distal part. Free portion of hydrotheca highly variable. Hydrothecal aperture circular, rim even, frequently with many renovations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE6252DFFDB4D130BA8F9E7FC4216CE" blockId="7.[151,1437,1357,1994]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Gonothecae solitary, resting on stem and branches. Gonotheca elongate, with large, circular, distal aperture (
<figureCitation id="136239A8FFDB4D130BF0F9C3FF3016CE" box="[159,246,1645,1670]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[266,1353,236,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[208,1380,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acryptolaria crassicaulis (Allman, 1888): A, hydrotheca; B, macrobasic mastigophore nematocyst (arrow). Cryptolarella abyssicola (Allman, 1888): C-D, hydrothecae; E, gonotheca. Lafoea dumosa (Fleming, 1820): F, hydrotheca; G, detail of basal part of hydrotheca; H, isorhiza nematocyst. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, C-F), 100 µm (G), 10 µm (B, H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1044778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Gonothecal wall with fine transversal striation (
<figureCitation id="136239A8FFDB4D13084FF9C3FCB116CE" box="[800,887,1645,1670]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[266,1353,236,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[208,1380,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Acryptolaria crassicaulis (Allman, 1888): A, hydrotheca; B, macrobasic mastigophore nematocyst (arrow). Cryptolarella abyssicola (Allman, 1888): C-D, hydrothecae; E, gonotheca. Lafoea dumosa (Fleming, 1820): F, hydrotheca; G, detail of basal part of hydrotheca; H, isorhiza nematocyst. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, C-F), 100 µm (G), 10 µm (B, H)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1044778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE6252DFFDB4D130BA8F93FFCD016E2" blockId="7.[151,1437,1357,1994]" box="[199,790,1681,1706]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Only one category of microbasic euryteles observed.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE6252DFFDB4D130BA8F918FC9916BA" blockId="7.[151,1437,1357,1994]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Measurements (in µm). 
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130ABDF91BFD931686" box="[466,597,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Hydrotheca</emphasis>
: diameter at aperture 140–180. 
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D1308D7F91BFBF51686" box="[952,1075,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Gonotheca</emphasis>
: length, 2100–2400, diameter at aperture 360–400. 
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130A06F977FE0816BA" box="[361,462,1753,1778]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cnidome</emphasis>
: microbasic euryteles, 8– 
<date id="FFE703EDFFDB4D130980F974FCD716B9" box="[751,785,1754,1778]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">9 x</date>
3–3.5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34376A6FFDB4D130BA8F953FD301772" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE6252DFFDB4D130BA8F953FD301772" blockId="7.[151,1437,1357,1994]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130BA8F953FEFD175E" bold="true" box="[199,315,1789,1814]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC858DCFFDB4D130A1DF950FDA3175E" box="[370,613,1789,1814]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Marques, A. C., Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Migotto, A. E. (2005) Revision of the genus Cryptolarella Stechow, 1913 (Lafoeidae, Leptothecata, Hydrozoa). Journal of Natural History, 39, 709 - 722. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400001467" type="journal article">
Marques 
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130AB4F950FDD2175E" box="[475,532,1789,1814]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al,</emphasis>
(2005)
</bibRefCitation>
for a revision and wide discussion on the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C595EAEFFDB4D130FE6F953FAE6175E" authorityName="Stechow" authorityYear="1913" box="[1161,1312,1789,1814]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Lafoeidae" genus="Cryptolarella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130FE6F953FAE6175E" box="[1161,1312,1789,1814]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cryptolarella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as for a re-description of the 
<typeStatus id="54E29B8FFFDB4D130AD3F88CFE2A1772" box="[444,492,1826,1850]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
material of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34376A6FFDB4D130BA8F8EBFD3E1782" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BE6252DFFDB4D130BA8F8EBFD3E1782" blockId="7.[151,1437,1357,1994]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130BA8F8EBFE3E1716" bold="true" box="[199,504,1861,1886]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ecology and distribution.</emphasis>
This is a deep-water species, found at depths from 200 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC858DCFFDB4D130FEFF8EBFADE1716" author="Millard" box="[1152,1304,1861,1886]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Millard, N. A. H. (1975) Monograph on the Hydroida of southern Africa. Annals of the South African Museum, 68, 1 - 513." type="journal article" year="1975">Millard 1975</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<quantity id="4CA188C8FFDB4D130E29F8EBFA5A1715" box="[1350,1436,1861,1886]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.327999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="6328.0">6328 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC858DCFFDB4D130BF1F8C4FE8317CA" author="Vervoort" box="[158,325,1898,1922]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Vervoort, W. (1972) Hydroids from the Theta, Vema and Yelcho cruises of the Lamont Doherty geological observatory. Zoologische Verhandelingen, Leiden, 120, 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1972">Vervoort 1972</bibRefCitation>
) in scattered records from the Antarctic, Atlantic, Pacific and Indian oceans (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC858DCFFDB4D130F9AF8C4FF1217EE" author="Marques" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Marques, A. C., Pena Cantero, A. L. &amp; Migotto, A. E. (2005) Revision of the genus Cryptolarella Stechow, 1913 (Lafoeidae, Leptothecata, Hydrozoa). Journal of Natural History, 39, 709 - 722. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400001467" type="journal article" year="2005">
Marques 
<emphasis id="B92DF93FFFDB4D130E0EF8C4FA5A17CA" box="[1377,1436,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
). The present material comes from the Porcupine Seabight and the Porcupine Abyssal Plain, collected at depths from 
<quantity id="4CA188C8FFDB4D130A4BF81CFE111781" box="[292,471,1969,1994]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8114999999999997" metricValueMax="4.853" metricValueMin="2.77" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="3811.5" valueMax="4853.0" valueMin="2770.0">2770 to 4853 m</quantity>
, with gonothecae in May.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
